ch.ecma.csta.binding

Class HookswitchEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject
      • ch.ecma.csta.binding.HookswitchEvent
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class HookswitchEvent
extends ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject
implements java.io.Serializable
    Indicates that the switch has changed the device's hookswitch status. This event is not sent if your device explicitly goes onhook with a SetHookswitchStatus request. It only occurs when all other parties on the call drop or are dropped. The switch then automatically sets the device's hookswitch status to on hook.

    This event may be generated in any one of the following ways:

    • The application sent SetHookswitchStatus request.
    • The hookswitch status has been changed manually.
    • The computing function has invoked a call control service that indirectly affected the hookswitch.
